g.text: EleanorRank4Convo2 begins.

g.title: j2109806441
g.text: O Drifter! O vagabond of time and space! How welcome your presence is on this little screen of mine!

g.title: j2371610510
g.text: Hi, Eleanor.

g.title: j2168673483
g.text: Brb, Kalymos is playing with the cords again and she might disconn [End.]

g.title: j3238353629
g.text: Hey matey.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j427459395
g.text: Guess what.

g.title: j2695924065
g.text: You’ve got a question about what life is like in the future?

g.title: j1665348187
g.text: You've grown a tail.

g.title: j4221675562
g.text: Ugh. I’m so tediously bloody predictable.

g.title: j3942268872
g.text: ... you'd like that, wouldn't you?

g.title: j635823116
g.text: Yes, I do. Yet another one. But this is a really big one, so bear with me, okay?

g.title: j3604560786
g.text: Alas, no. My bottom has not been improved by the addition of a tail. It cannot be improved, for it is already perfect.

g.title: j2762022520
g.text: I’ll do my best.

g.title: j840337770
g.text: However, I did have a question for you.

g.title: j407747881
g.text: Good. Great. So.

g.title: j3895247629
g.text: How do relationships work in your time? I mean, is it all the usual ‘two or more adults get together with varying degrees of solemnization’ stuff? Or are there all sorts of rules about who can be with who?

g.title: j3854699252
g.text: That’s not something I’ve looked into.

g.title: j1061614961
g.text: It depends on the culture.

g.title: j2232471650
g.text: … why would you ask that?

g.title: j1247149444
g.text: Gosh.

g.title: j684397881
g.text: Right. Of course.

g.title: j1915671247
g.text: Check boolean EleanorEntrati

g.title: j1878918837
g.text: I know you were isolated in Duviri, but I had no idea you were THAT isolated.

g.title: j588599863
g.text: Let me try another tack.

g.title: j1517042173
g.text: Those two on Deimos, Father and Mother. They’re a married couple. They may be gigantic Infested former Orokin whatnots, but they’re very clearly and painfully MARRIED in exactly the same way my mum and dad are.

g.title: j1915671247->j1517042173
g.text: true

g.title: j265980665
g.text: From the bits and pieces I've gleaned from your mind, I still see standard pairings of people. Folks who are very clearly and painfully MARRIED in exactly the same way my mum and dad are.

g.title: j1915671247->j265980665
g.text: false

g.title: j866737005
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j597040285
g.text: Let's see...

g.title: j3053058237
g.text: So was that standard for Orokin?

g.title: j2137367506
g.text: I'm sincerely sorry if I've caused you any upset by asking.

g.title: j3260597765
g.text: Okay. So where you come from, would it be normal for a person to be in a relationship with, say, a Cephalon?

g.title: j3378279781
g.text: Orokin were all about rules and taboos. They loved hierarchy. Relationships couldn’t cross social lines. A Dax couldn’t be with an Orokin noble, say.

g.title: j477365850
g.text: I could try to drag Ordis back here in time if you'd like to try to find out...

g.title: j3077442768
g.text: … I’ve never heard of it, and I’m not sure how it would work.

g.title: j4190965861
g.text: I am trying to ask a THEORETICAL question!

g.title: j2714601011
g.text: Damn. Let me try again.

g.title: j1623051089
g.text: I'm not aching to grind myself against your glassy chum, however charming he may be

g.title: j1199786419
g.text: Make up someone from your time who’s both female and dangerous. Strong, too. Like Major Rusalka without the demonic possession.

g.title: j1972937571
g.text: I'm trying, and failing, to ask you about POWER IMBALANCES

g.title: j1058423392
g.text: A Grineer sniper?

g.title: j3251219338
g.text: A Dax?

g.title: j3154420596
g.text: Okay. Let’s say there’s a Grineer sniper lady and she falls for a human. And it’s mutual. Star crossed lovers. Desperately tragic. Could they be together?

g.title: j3122979420
g.text: Okay. Let’s say there’s a Dax soldier lady and she falls for a lowly human. And it’s mutual. Star crossed lovers. Desperately tragic. Could they be together?

g.title: j2332006895
g.text: If it was what they both wanted, sure.

g.title: j2874481624
g.text: Why not?

g.title: j423791674
g.text: I’d like to see anyone try to stop them.

g.title: j191358236
g.text: Yes, but it would be hard.

g.title: j1362364441
g.text: I’m tying myself in knots here.

g.title: j408572322
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3660105217
g.text: Is it normal where you come from for people to get together with partners who are far more powerful and dangerous than they are? Like in ‘Gumbly and the Dragon’s Socks’ when the elf prince ends up married to the giant?

g.title: j3003744209
g.text: Thank you.

g.title: j1419029823
g.text: … you don’t know what I’m talking about, do you.

g.title: j1482599185
g.text: Question: can two people with wildly differing physiques and lethality levels be in a relationship? Answer: yes.

g.title: j820594922
g.text: Actually, I’m pretty sure I do.

g.title: j1937511168
g.text: Not really, no.

g.title: j2446709672
g.text: That's all I wanted to know.

g.title: j3471037362
g.text: I don’t want to ruin your day. Sorry.

g.title: j3144203487
g.text: I'd better stop. I'm in danger of making a complete berk of myself.

g.title: j1094334530
g.text: Can I be allowed a self-pitying rant?

g.title: j1304887419
g.text: Rant away.

g.title: j4182469746
g.text: I don't have the time for this, sorry. [End.]

g.title: j1780020909
g.text: I am NOT saying my life is meaningless without someone to share it with

g.title: j840536252
g.text: I am NOT defined by who I choose to love

g.title: j2386272286
g.text: I am sufficient unto myself

g.title: j1361181782
g.text: BUT HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO EVEN ENTERTAIN THE POSSIBILITY OF A RELATIONSHIP WHEN I COULD LITERALLY KILL SOMEONE BY ACCIDENT IF I GOT CARRIED AWAY

g.title: j1093003795
g.text: Welcome to Eleanor and her horny mantis problems

g.title: j2194511874
g.text: If I ever find that Entrati bastard I will turn his balls into earrings. If he has any balls.

g.title: j19110296
g.text: You could always date someone else in the Hex.

g.title: j3779772567
g.text: Hold on. You’re single because you’re worried about hurting someone?

g.title: j1242100208
g.text: OMFS

g.title: j2507061528
g.text: Yes.

g.title: j2264702358
g.text: I AM LITERALLY BITING MY TONGUE SO I DON'T LAUGH

g.title: j813944327
g.text: You know what I am better than I do, I think. I’m a Protoframe. I’m a partially transformed war machine, and it feels like it’s getting less partial by the day.

g.title: j958587448
g.text: The only one of those four I could even CONSIDER dating is Aoi and that's complicated because of Arthur

g.title: j1982704141
g.text: Whoever designed poor ‘Nyx’ was building a killer. That’s me, now. Efficient. Lethal. Cuddly as a claymore.

g.title: j1399612021
g.text: Bless you for suggesting that but no, not in a million years

g.title: j1277376940
g.text: All very well when it comes to the day job, but at the office party who’s going to kiss a walking deathtrap under the mistletoe?

g.title: j2721888813
g.text: This accidental hurting you’re worried about. Has it ever happened? Have you ever hurt someone you were with?

g.title: j1108656603
g.text: I mean, at least the good news is that if there was an accident, nobody in Höllvania stays dead after the reset...

g.title: j3999254429
g.text: No it hasn’t happened because I haven’t bloody let it. OK?

g.title: j2360620581
g.text: No partners, no casualties. Not worth the risk.

g.title: j1470761302
g.text: I hadn't considered that.

g.title: j1058579620
g.text: I’d rather be lonely than steeped in guilt, thanks.

g.title: j2817344923
g.text: Our memories persist, though.

g.title: j916215232
g.text: So you’ve been single since the Entrati shots?

g.title: j1564297202
g.text: I don't think anyone would want to be in a relationship with someone who bit their head off once, even if it got better.

g.title: j1230470874
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j3982341078
g.text: Lua wept. I need a drink now.

g.title: j3743832658
g.text: Correct. A trade-off I am quite willing to make.

g.title: j2190710896
g.text: Sorry. I’m not sure talking about this was a good idea.

g.title: j838651017
g.text: I think I need to be on my own for a bit.
